José Luis Gómez (actor) https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jos%C3%A9_Luis_G%C3%B3mez_(actor) 0 José Luis Gómez García (born 19 April 1940) is a Spanish film actor and director. He has appeared in 33 films since 1968. At the 1976 Cannes Film Festival, he won the award for Best Actor in the film Pascual Duarte. Gómez was elected to Seat Z of the Real Academia Española on 1 December 2011; he took up his seat on 26 January 2014.
